Wash and dry produce. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(finely diced). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Zest half the @lime{1}; quarter lime.

Drain and roughly chop @pulled pork{8%ounce}(roughly chopped) into smaller pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until pork is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use ½ tsp salt.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @pork ramen stock concentrate{1}, and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until broth has thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and @pepper{} if needed.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer pork filling to a #medium bowl{}, leaving broth behind. Cook until broth has reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat; cover to keep warm.

== Pico de Gallo ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, lime zest, juice from half the lime, and @olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

== Crispy Tacos ==

Place @flour tortillas{6} on a clean work surface. Sprinkle one half of each tortilla with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}; top with pork filling. Fold tortillas in half to create tacos.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium heat. Add tacos and cook until tortillas are crisped, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

== To Serve ==

Divide birria broth between small #serving bowls{}.

> If needed, return pan to medium heat until broth is warmed through before serving.

Divide tacos between plates; serve with pico de gallo (draining first), remaining lime wedges, and birria broth for dipping.